<div class="prose-content max-w-3xl">

  <h2>Our commitment</h2>
  <p>Scoonie Medical Practice is committed to making this website accessible in accordance with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA. We want as many people as possible to be able to use this website, regardless of ability or technology.</p>

  <h2>What we've done</h2>
  <p>This website has been designed and built with accessibility in mind. We have:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Used clear, plain English throughout (target reading age of 12 or below)</li>
    <li>Ensured all pages are navigable by keyboard alone</li>
    <li>Provided a skip-to-content link on every page</li>
    <li>Used sufficient colour contrast for all text and interactive elements</li>
    <li>Made all interactive elements at least 44x44 pixels on mobile devices</li>
    <li>Added descriptive text to all links (no 'click here')</li>
    <li>Labelled all form fields clearly</li>
    <li>Used semantic HTML throughout for screen reader compatibility</li>
    <li>Ensured the site works well on all screen sizes and devices</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>BSL users</h2>
  <p>If you use British Sign Language, you can contact us using the <a href="{{ site.bslLink }}" rel="noopener noreferrer">ContactSCOTLAND BSL video relay service</a>. This free service lets you make a video call to a BSL interpreter, who will then contact us on your behalf.</p>

  <h2>Interpreting and translation</h2>
  <p>If you need an interpreter for your appointment, please let us know when you book and we will arrange this. NHS Inform provides health information in <a href="https://www.nhsinform.scot/translations/" rel="noopener noreferrer">multiple languages</a>.</p>

  <h2>Visiting Leven Health Centre</h2>
  <p>The health centre has:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Step-free access to the building</li>
    <li>Accessible toilet facilities</li>
    <li>A hearing loop at reception</li>
    <li>Free patient parking</li>
  </ul>
  <p>If you have any access requirements, please let our reception team know when booking your appointment.</p>

  <h2>Known limitations</h2>
  <p>We are aware of the following limitations:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Some older PDF documents may not be fully accessible to screen readers. We are working to replace these with accessible versions.</li>
    <li>The embedded map on our contact page is provided by OpenStreetMap and may have limited screen reader support.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Feedback and contact</h2>
  <p>If you have difficulty using this website or would like to report an accessibility issue, please <a href="/contact/get-in-touch/">get in touch</a>. We take accessibility seriously and will do our best to resolve any issues.</p>
  <p>You can also contact us by phone on <a href="tel:{{ site.phone | replace(' ', '') }}">{{ site.phone }}</a>, Monday to Friday, 08:00 to 18:00.</p>

  <h2>Enforcement</h2>
  <p>If you are not satisfied with our response to an accessibility concern, you can contact the <a href="https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Equality Advisory Support Service (EASS)</a>.</p>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-mid mt-8">This statement was last updated on 17 March 2026.</p>

</div>
